On Sun, Sep 19, 1999 at 08:30:59AM -0000, Eric Smith wrote:
> Does anyone have any examples of how to use the Linux Socket Filter?  Yes,
> I have read the documentation, and it doesn't really address my questions.
If you want to use it from user-space, the best thing would probably be to
modify the application to use libpcap. I think Alexey Kuznetsov has patches
to libpcap to make it do in-kernel filtering on Linux.
